There is one word in the 74-page document, however, that stood out to me: “invader.” Tarrant’s words are both lucid and chillingly familiar.
His references to immigrants as invaders find echoes in the language used by the president of the United States and far-right leaders across Europe.
In the faces of immigrants trying to raise families and build peaceful homes, Tarrant sees unarmed invaders bent on conquering his racially pristine homeland.
His alleged actions are the logical conclusion to the rhetoric of “American Carnage” and “The Death of Europe” promoted by prominent figures across the globe.
“The invaders must be removed from European soil, regardless from where they came or when they came.